2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 188
BY SENATOR ABRAHAM
A RESOLUTION
To commend and congratulate Marvin Self upon the occasion of his ninety-ninth birthday
and to recognize his remarkable life of service, achievement, and dedication to his
family, community, state, and nation.
WHEREAS, Marvin Self was born on May 28, 1927, in Beaumont, Texas, and in
1935 moved with his parents and two sisters to Evangeline, Louisiana, where he spent his
formative years; and
WHEREAS, while attending Iota High School, Marvin lettered in basketball and
track, competing in the 100-yard dash and the mile, demonstrating early the determination
and discipline that would define his life; and
WHEREAS, Marvin graduated from Iota High School in May 1945 and, at age
seventeen, forged his mother's signature to enlist in the United States Navy, serving
honorably in the Pacific Theater during the final months of World War II; and
WHEREAS, after his discharge in 1947, Marvin enrolled at McNeese Junior College,
where he met his future wife, Shirley Kerr, beginning a partnership that would last nearly
seven decades; and
WHEREAS, after graduating from McNeese in 1949, Marvin enrolled at Louisiana
State University, living in the dormitories beneath Tiger Stadium and rooming with Frank
Salter, who would later serve as district attorney of the Fourteenth Judicial District; and
WHEREAS, while at LSU, Marvin was called from the inactive reserve to serve in
the Korean Conflict, spending one year and one day aboard the Admiral's flagship in Hawaii
before being discharged in 1951; and
WHEREAS, upon returning to Lake Charles, Marvin married Shirley Kerr on
September 5, 1951, and together they raised four children: Malcolm, Melanie, Douglas, and
Richard; and
WHEREAS, Marvin was deeply involved in his children's activities, serving in
