leadership roles in Cub Scouts, Boy Scouts, Explorer Scouts, Camp Fire Girls, Little League
baseball, and church basketball, and as leader of Explorer Post 54, he brought the group to
the National Explorer Olympics in Colorado after winning the state title; and
WHEREAS, Marvin began his professional career with Olin Mathieson from 1951
to 1954, and in 1954 joined Dresser Magcobar, where he worked until 1986; and
WHEREAS, in 1963, Marvin was part of the crew that drilled Alaska's first
successful oil well on the North Slope, spending three months on the job and returning to
Lake Charles just one day before the Fairbanks earthquake; and
WHEREAS, in 1986, Marvin founded All Star Consultants, managing the company
until his retirement from the oilfield in 2013 at the age of eighty-six; and
WHEREAS, Marvin has served on the boards of several oilfield-related companies,
contributing his expertise to the advancement of the industry; and
WHEREAS, Marvin is an active member of St. Michael's Episcopal Church, where
he served on missionary teams to Honduras, helping to build and renovate churches and
forming a deep connection to the country and its people; and
WHEREAS, Marvin's love for Honduras led him to purchase a home there, where
he spent several months each year for decades; and
WHEREAS, Marvin is a world traveler who has circumnavigated the globe multiple
times, including traveling across Russia to China on the Trans-Siberian Railroad, reflecting
his lifelong curiosity and adventurous spirit; and
WHEREAS, in retirement, Marvin enjoys day trading, gardening, and caring for his
two beloved dogs, Scout and Rafa; and
WHEREAS, the Louisiana Senate wishes to honor Marvin Self for his extraordinary
life, his service to his country, his devotion to his family, his contributions to his community,
and the example he sets for all Louisianians; and
WHEREAS, May 28, 2026, marks the ninety-ninth birthday of Marvin Self, a
milestone worthy of the highest recognition.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby commend and congratulate Marvin Self upon the occasion of his ninety-ninth
birthday and does hereby extend its heartfelt appreciation for his lifetime of service.
